[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The print format string in `run_demo()` is `f"dur={payload['trend_duration_days']:>5.0f}d "`, which produces an integer width-5 right-padded number, never the literal string `"..."`. Similarly, the JSON payload's `trend_duration_days` is a `Decimal` from `_to_decimal(round(..., 1))`, never a literal `"..."` string. A learner who runs `python chapter12.04.py` against the in-memory mocks and sees actual numbers (where the doc shows ellipses) may pause to wonder whether the doc is stale or whether they have the wrong configuration.
